commentBody:
@Amy 

I pronounce TACO more like it is in Spanish, with an open "ah" sound, so I guess that's why it doesn't rhyme for me.

Thank you for replying. I can now see where many pronounce it "taw-co," though it had never occurred to me.

@Vaer 

Strange, since I've never noticed the comments for Wordplay *ever* being closed.

I've been playing from the archives, and most of *those* comment sections are still open after more than a year.

@MB 

I do believe kk knows that....and I agree with kk that this puzzle is a cut above the usual  Monday fare, meaning it was more complex and clever.

kkseattle winked when hitting Submit.

@Eric Hougland 

HOP, SKI, PANDA JUMP is an annual triathlon in Southwest China.  After the event, the PANDA eats, shoots and leaves.




The emus diet consists mainly of comments that are deemed too brief.

@Vaer 
Oh, yeah?  I got jumped on when I did it.

(I no longer bother with the Mini.)

@HeathieJ 
Thank you! It really did go even better than I could have hoped, including some people who were at our wedding 40 years ago who I haven’t seen for about 25 years due to distance, children etc. So emotional.
Yes, I think I said before that I know the streak is a purely personal thing that has no value to anyone else, but I was a little reluctant to drop mine without a fight.

@Cap’n Dan Mathews 
I don't understand why people are making demands as to what crossword constructors can create, or what the NYT can publish (not just you, there were ruder ones yesterday).

If you don't like a puzzle, just don't do it. The world isn't going to collapse if you skip one.

@A hobbit 

Congratulations on your first gold star! As HeathieJ said, you'll have many more in your future. 

Have fun!
